This paper deals with submodular optimization, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses machine learning applications, which suggests that it could belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with data summarization and maximum coverage problems, which are classic topics in data mining (cs.DM). Finally, the paper presents algorithms that use heuristics to improve efficiency, which suggests that it could belong to the category of information theory (cs.IT).
